#This is the step that actually defines the simulation box in the output structure:

gmx editconf -f DMSO_2000.pdb -o DMSO_2000_6p2nm.gro -box 6.2 6.2 6.2

# study nic-nic interaction using RDF
gmx rdf -f production_whole.trr -s production.tpr -n index.ndx -ref 'group 2' -sel 'group 2' -selrpos mol_com -seltype mol_com -o rdf_nic_nic.xvg -cn cn_nic_nic.xvg

✅ 2) Continue but extend the simulation longer

Checkpoint only continues until your .tpr ends (its nsteps).

So you must first extend the .tpr.

Step A: extend the tpr (example: extend by 10 ns)

With dt=0.002 ps, 10 ns = 10,000 ps = 5,000,000 steps:

gmx convert-tpr -s production.tpr -extend 10000 -o production_ext.tpr


(-extend is in ps)

Step B: run using the extended tpr + same checkpoint
gmx mdrun -s production_ext.tpr -deffnm production -cpi production.cpt


✅ Output continues in the same files.
